  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Metrics Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Metrics are an interpretation of a measure or a set of measures that you use to guide your project.&amp;nbsp;Interpreting&#xD;
    what level of quality this indicates and how it reflects the team's progress within the current iteration is a metric.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Benefits of using metrics:&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Help to communicate effectively&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Guide in the tunning of estimations.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Help in making informed trade-off decisions.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Recommended Metrics&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Development productivity&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Velocity: Number of delivered points by iteration&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Cost and schedule estimate and variance&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Effort: Actual effort spent per iteration&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Cost: Cost per iteration&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Effort remaining: Track&amp;nbsp;project burndown&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Advice&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Consider only implementing a handfull of metrics that deliver value to the projects goal or software development&#xD;
    process.&amp;nbsp;Avoid collecting metrics that you will not act on&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
